To run in a virtualenv:
pip install virtualenv
virtualenv venv

Linux:
source venv/bin/activate

Windows:
.\venv\Scripts\activate

To get the packages:
pip install -r requirements.txt

In order to collect tweets you need a developer account on twitter.
Once you set that up make a file key.py and put in it:
consumer_key = 'your public key' 
consumer_secret = 'your private key'
access_token = 'your public access token'
access_secret = 'your private access token'

To run:
python bot.py

To use recently pulled data in bot.py change:
USED_SET = CURRENT_SET

To use all data accumulated in bot.py change:
USED_SET=ALL_DATA

To not run the bot bot.py change:
RUN_BOT = False

To not run Tweet collection in bot.py change:
COLLECT_DATA = False

